{
  "esm": "0.6.0",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "nearest_generator_argmin",
    "description": "KEYSTONE value-invention fixture (RFC semiring-faq-unified-ir §5.5 / §5.7 rule 6; CONFORMANCE_SPEC.md §5.5.1 rule 6; bead ess-os1, mpas-scvt epic esd-e5m): the arg-witness reducer `argmin` — a build-time value-invention op that emits the nearest-generator INDEX per point. NET-NEW because the closed semiring registry (§5.1) returns VALUES and the value-invention primitives distinct/skolem/rank (§5.5) return SETS — neither returns the ARG. `assign[i] = argmin_g dist(point_i, gen_g)` over the points × generators candidate join is a per-element CONST-cadence INTEGER buffer (exactly like the §A.8 bin-Skolem `:map` buffers `src_bin`/`tgt_bin`), materialised ONCE at setup through the value-invention front-door (value_invention.{jl,rs,py}). The per-iteration STEP — the distance `dist(point_i, gen_g)` — is a declarative FAQ over the const coordinate factors (`*`/`-`/`+`); the host loop over generators is RHS-only; the argmin reduction itself is the allowed irreducible leaf (like intersect_polygon §8.1, it cannot be written in the semiring algebra). The NORMATIVE tie-break is the SMALLEST generator ID — equal distances resolve to the lower index — so the emitted assignment buffer is BYTE-IDENTICAL across Julia/Rust/Python irrespective of enumeration order (§5.7 byte-identical determinism). Two models: (1) NearestGeneratorArgmin — the unpruned full points × generators argmin with a DELIBERATE equidistant tie at point 3 (1.5 between generators at 1.0 and 2.0) that the tie-break resolves to the lower generator; (2) NearestGeneratorBinned — the bin-Skolem-pruned variant where the argmin's `join` (`floor` quantization + `skolem` bin key + value-equality equi-join, §5.3) restricts each point's candidate generators to those sharing its integer lat-lon bin (the SCVT broad phase). Squared Euclidean distance keeps the metric a single-multiply FAQ (no `^`/`sqrt` needed) and every distance an exact dyadic so the tie is bit-exact. STRUCTURAL fixture: the coordinate factors are supplied by each binding's front-door test (mirroring edge_enumeration_area_eff.esm / conservative_regrid_overlap_join.esm); cross-binding byte-identity of the emitted integer buffer IS the conformance contract.",
    "authors": [
      "EarthSciSerialization/polecats/gastown.slit"
    ],
    "tags": [
      "aggregate",
      "argmin",
      "arg-witness",
      "value-invention",
      "nearest-generator",
      "tie-break",
      "bin-skolem",
      "spatial-join",
      "mpas-scvt",
      "determinism",
      "conformance",
      "schema",
      "ess-os1"
    ]
  },
  "models": {
    "NearestGeneratorArgmin": {
      "index_sets": {
        "points": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 4
        },
        "generators": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 3
        }
      },
      "variables": {
        "px": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["points"],
          "description": "Point longitudes. A const coordinate factor read only inside the declarative distance FAQ (never a raw join comparison)."
        },
        "py": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["points"],
          "description": "Point latitudes."
        },
        "gx": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["generators"],
          "description": "Generator longitudes (the Voronoi seeds the points are assigned to)."
        },
        "gy": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["generators"],
          "description": "Generator latitudes."
        },
        "assign": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["points"],
          "description": "Nearest-generator INDEX of each point: assign[i] = argmin_g dist(point_i, gen_g). A value-invention arg-witness output — an integer 1-based generator id buffer materialised at setup (CONST cadence) and dropped from the ODE, exactly as the bin-Skolem `src_bin`/`tgt_bin` buffers are. The §5.7 rule-6 smallest-generator-id tie-break makes it byte-identical across bindings."
        }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "NEAREST-GENERATOR ASSIGNMENT — assign[i] = argmin_g dist(point_i, gen_g) over the FULL points × generators candidate set (unpruned). A per-element map (output i, no contraction at the outer level) whose body is the `argmin` arg-witness reducer: it contracts the inner range `g` over `generators`, evaluates the squared-Euclidean distance FAQ dist = (px[i]-gx[g])² + (py[i]-gy[g])² at each candidate (squared so the metric is `*`/`-`/`+` only — argmin is invariant to the monotone square, no `sqrt`), and returns the witnessing generator index `arg:\"g\"`. Equidistant generators resolve to the SMALLEST id (§5.7 rule 6): point 3 at 1.5 is exactly 0.25 from both generator 2 (at 1.0) and generator 3 (at 2.0) → generator 2.",
          "lhs": { "op": "index", "args": ["assign", "i"] },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "ranges": { "i": { "from": "points" } },
            "args": ["px", "py", "gx", "gy"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "argmin",
              "args": ["px", "py", "gx", "gy"],
              "arg": "g",
              "ranges": { "g": { "from": "generators" } },
              "expr": {
                "op": "+",
                "args": [
                  {
                    "op": "*",
                    "args": [
                      { "op": "-", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["px", "i"] }, { "op": "index", "args": ["gx", "g"] }] },
                      { "op": "-", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["px", "i"] }, { "op": "index", "args": ["gx", "g"] }] }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "op": "*",
                    "args": [
                      { "op": "-", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["py", "i"] }, { "op": "index", "args": ["gy", "g"] }] },
                      { "op": "-", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["py", "i"] }, { "op": "index", "args": ["gy", "g"] }] }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    "NearestGeneratorBinned": {
      "index_sets": {
        "points": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 4
        },
        "generators": {
          "kind": "interval",
          "size": 3
        }
      },
      "variables": {
        "px": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["points"],
          "description": "Point longitudes."
        },
        "py": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["points"],
          "description": "Point latitudes."
        },
        "gx": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["generators"],
          "description": "Generator longitudes."
        },
        "gy": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": ["generators"],
          "description": "Generator latitudes."
        },
        "binw": {
          "type": "parameter",
          "shape": [],
          "description": "Bin width in degrees — the integer lat-lon quantization step of the broad phase (§A.8). Shared by points and generators so a common bin key means they fall in the same bucket."
        },
        "point_bin": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["points"],
          "description": "Integer bin key of each point: skolem(\"bin\", floor(px/binw), floor(py/binw)) — the §A.8 broad-phase quantization. The equi-join column the argmin's candidate prune joins on."
        },
        "gen_bin": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["generators"],
          "description": "Integer bin key of each generator — identically quantized, so a shared key means a point and generator fall in the same broad-phase bucket."
        },
        "assign_binned": {
          "type": "state",
          "shape": ["points"],
          "description": "Nearest-generator INDEX restricted to same-bin candidates: assign_binned[i] = argmin_{g : point_bin[i] = gen_bin[g]} dist(point_i, gen_g). The argmin's `join` (bin-Skolem equi-join, §5.3) prunes the candidate generators to the point's bin before the distance reduction — the SCVT broad phase. CONST-cadence integer buffer, byte-identical across bindings (§5.7 rule 6)."
        }
      },
      "equations": [
        {
          "_comment": "BROAD PHASE 1 — bin each POINT to an integer lat-lon bin key (floor quantization + skolem mint), exactly the §A.8 `src_bin` map.",
          "lhs": { "op": "index", "args": ["point_bin", "i"] },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "ranges": { "i": { "from": "points" } },
            "args": ["px", "py", "binw"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "skolem",
              "args": [
                "bin",
                { "op": "floor", "args": [{ "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["px", "i"] }, "binw"] }] },
                { "op": "floor", "args": [{ "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["py", "i"] }, "binw"] }] }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "BROAD PHASE 2 — bin each GENERATOR identically (same binw quantization), the §A.8 `tgt_bin` map.",
          "lhs": { "op": "index", "args": ["gen_bin", "g"] },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "output_idx": ["g"],
            "ranges": { "g": { "from": "generators" } },
            "args": ["gx", "gy", "binw"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "skolem",
              "args": [
                "bin",
                { "op": "floor", "args": [{ "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["gx", "g"] }, "binw"] }] },
                { "op": "floor", "args": [{ "op": "/", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["gy", "g"] }, "binw"] }] }
              ]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "_comment": "NARROW PHASE — assign_binned[i] = argmin_g dist over ONLY the same-bin candidate generators. The argmin's `join` is the bin-Skolem value-equality equi-join (§5.3): point_bin[i] = gen_bin[g] gates which (i,g) pairs enter the distance reduction (the broad phase), then the squared-Euclidean FAQ + smallest-id tie-break pick the winner (the narrow phase). Builds directly on the landed bin-Skolem join + front-door.",
          "lhs": { "op": "index", "args": ["assign_binned", "i"] },
          "rhs": {
            "op": "aggregate",
            "output_idx": ["i"],
            "ranges": { "i": { "from": "points" } },
            "args": ["px", "py", "gx", "gy", "point_bin", "gen_bin"],
            "expr": {
              "op": "argmin",
              "args": ["px", "py", "gx", "gy"],
              "arg": "g",
              "ranges": { "g": { "from": "generators" } },
              "join": [
                { "on": [["point_bin", "gen_bin"]] }
              ],
              "expr": {
                "op": "+",
                "args": [
                  {
                    "op": "*",
                    "args": [
                      { "op": "-", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["px", "i"] }, { "op": "index", "args": ["gx", "g"] }] },
                      { "op": "-", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["px", "i"] }, { "op": "index", "args": ["gx", "g"] }] }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "op": "*",
                    "args": [
                      { "op": "-", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["py", "i"] }, { "op": "index", "args": ["gy", "g"] }] },
                      { "op": "-", "args": [{ "op": "index", "args": ["py", "i"] }, { "op": "index", "args": ["gy", "g"] }] }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
